FuncDef:
The nat session-log elog-version v2 command enables the system to send flow logs in the version 2 format.
The undo nat session-log elog-version v2 command disables the system from sending flow logs in the version 2 format.
By default, the system sends flow logs in the version 1 format.
ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
The system allows the VSUF-80/VSUF-160/VSUI-160-E/VSUI-400/VSUI-400-E/VSUI-400A/VSUI-400A-E/VSUI-400-S/VSUI-400A-S to send flow logs in the version 2 format. By default, the system supports the sending of flow logs in the version 1 format.
Precautions
This command is applicable only to the VSUF-80/VSUF-160/VSUI-160-E/VSUI-400/VSUI-400-E/VSUI-400A/VSUI-400A-E/VSUI-400-S/VSUI-400A-S.
